ng\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"img\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"width\";s:3:\"190\";s:6:\"height\";s:3:\"130\";s:3:\"src\";s:80:\"https://marketplace.appthemes.com/files/2013/06/ACFprivacy-thumbnail-190x130.png\";s:5:\"class\";s:54:\"attachment-post-thumbnail img-responsive wp-post-image\";s:3:\"alt\";s:20:\"ACFprivacy-thumbnail\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}s:5:\"price\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"9\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:6:\"rating\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"votes\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"rank\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"75\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Mohsin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2277:\"<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\">Hides private content (fields) from users without certain Roles or Membership Packs and replaces it with another content.</span></p>\n<p>The plugin improves <a title=\"Advanced Custom Fields for ClassiPress\" href=\"http://marketplace.appthemes.com/plugins/advanced-custom-fields-for-classipress/\" target=\"_blank\">ACFCP</a> build-in &#8220;For Logged-in&#8221; option and provides following additional options for each field:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\"><span style=\"color: #ff4700\"><strong>Placeholder</strong></span>: Text, which not trusted users will see on page (for ex. &#8220;This field hidden for not logged-in!&#8221;). If empty, the field will not shown for not trusted at all. Also works with <a title=\"Advanced Custom Fields for ClassiPress\" href=\"http://marketplace.appthemes.com/plugins/advanced-custom-fields-for-classipress/\" target=\"_blank\">ACFCP</a> build-in option &#8220;For Logged-in&#8221;.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\"><span style=\"color: #ff4700\"><strong>Allowed Memberships</strong></span>: Membership Packs IDs delimited by commas to display this field. If empty or user is Admin &#8211; there will no restrictions by Membership.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\"><span style=\"color: #ff4700\"><strong>Allowed Roles</strong></span>: WP Roles delimited by commas to display this field. If field is empty or user is Admin &#8211; there will no restrictions by roles.</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p>For example you can use it for field &#8220;Phone Number&#8221;, if you want hide this field from not logged-in users or from search engines and other bots. They are will see only &#8220;Placeholder&#8221; text, which you can set for each field separately.</p>\n<p>Ideal for use in pair with ACFCP Add-on &#8220;ACF :: Hyperlink&#8221;.</p>\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\">Requires </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5em\" title=\"Advanced Custom Fields for ClassiPress\" href=\"http://marketplace.appthemes.com/plugins/advanced-custom-fields-for-classipress/\" target=\"_blank\">ACFCP</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em\"> 2.3+, ClassiPress 3.2+  WordPress 3.0+.</span></p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AppthemesMarketplace/~4/TEfHzOGa-OU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://